# Commit Message Convention

- Use gitmoji shortcode + one concise line.
- Format: `:<gitmoji>: <single-line description>`
- Keep subject imperative and specific.

# Preferred Gitmojis

- `:sparkles:` new feature work
- `:card_file_box:` event data additions or updates
- `:lipstick:` visual/UI improvements
- `:bug:` bug fixes
- `:robot:` automated status/data updates from workflow
- `:memo:` docs and guidance updates
- `:wrench:` tooling and workflow configuration

# Examples

- `:sparkles: Add buyer-guide style event overview page`
- `:card_file_box: Update RopeLinked X status to sold_out`
- `:robot: Auto-update event statuses`

# Branch and PR Flow

- Never commit directly to protected branches (`main`, `staging`).
- Use prefixes: `feat/`, `fix/`, `docs/`, `data/`, `chore/`.
- Prefer `data/*` for event-data-only changes.
- Open PRs for all changes with a clear test/check plan.
